Commentary: |
  The Arabic root S K R has the basic sense of intoxication or
  sweetness (from which is derived the word sugar), thus allowing
  an esoteric interpretation of sakrah, "agony’, in the sense of
  "ecstasy'.
---
The agony of death cometh in truth.
